8bb26d65-47ef-4ca4-a9a8-55b76a1a2ee2.2031ef80-611b-4a7a-977d-6e431865c0de.prompt=SasHostUsername\: 8bb26d65-47ef-4ca4-a9a8-55b76a1a2ee2.3a919436-2343-4112-93cd-eef4f119fe5c.prompt=UsernamePrompt\: 8bb26d65-47ef-4ca4-a9a8-55b76a1a2ee2.4c4fa71f-312d-4076-bc85-9837cb84b2c5.description=
Runs a command and allows user to specify that it runs locally (in this case no port should be specified), via ssh, Global Shell, ROSH, Telnet, or RSH.

Inputs\:
host - hostname or ip address
port - port number for connecting to the host
username - username to connect as
password - password
protocol - the protocol used to run the command (can be one of ssh, ROSH, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH, local, WMI or NASConnectTelnet)
timeout - (optional, default 90 seconds) time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete; increase its value if you are getting incomplete output results or timeout
command - the command to execute
arguments - the arguments to pass to the command
environment - specifies environment variables/values that need to be defined when running command
startDir - the path to the starting directory
pty - (true, false) whether to use pty
privateKeyFile - The absolute path to the private key file for remote host.
sasHost - the host we want to run the ROSH command on
sasHostUsername - the username used to run the ROSH command on sasHost
usernamePrompt - the prompt that when seen should send the username; used by the Telnet protocol; when used by the NASConnectTelnet protocol, the default value is 'NAS Login\:'
passwordPrompt - the prompt that when given should send the password; used by the Telnet protocol; when used by the NASConnectTelnet protocol, the default value is 'Password\:'
outputPath - network accessible path used by the operation to store temporary files. If not specified it points to \\host\admin$\temp\'. If this     path is not accessible you should change it to use another share that the host local system account has write access to. By default, the path will have to be  changed on Windows 2000 systems
nasDevice - The NAS device to run the command on when using the NASConnect protocol.
nasDeviceConsoleMode - The NAS device console mode used to run the command scripts that run the command on the given NAS device. If this input is empty, command scripts are not used, and the connection to the NAS device and the command are issued directly in the console; this is not recommended, since its error handling capabilities are limited and it might result in success even when the command fails to execute. The values for this input can be found in the NAS web interface, as a drop-down list when a new command script is created (ex. Cisco IOS enable).

Responses\:
success - the command was executed successfully
failure - the command could not be executed

Extra Results\:
stdErr - the STDERR of the command
stdOut - the STDOUT of the command

Checks to see if a string matches a specific rule.

Inputs\:
matchType - The type of match to perform.
toMatch - The string to check if matches another string.
matchTo - The string to match against.
ignoreCase - Boolean value for whether or not to ignore case during match.

Responses\:
success - The String matched.
failure - The string did not match, or something went wrong.
8bb26d65-47ef-4ca4-a9a8-55b76a1a2ee2.b33c1ad7-1ad8-4d7d-82b7-d79a7ec4a472.prompt=Protocol\: 8bb26d65-47ef-4ca4-a9a8-55b76a1a2ee2.baeafb6b-cece-4a25-b885-9f321b37b888.prompt=Username\: 8bb26d65-47ef-4ca4-a9a8-55b76a1a2ee2.cc7169b4-3f6a-465f-813c-35f68d366691.prompt=Interface name\: 8bb26d65-47ef-4ca4-a9a8-55b76a1a2ee2.d84e68d4-e1f6-4015-946b-6901cda5f1cd.prompt=PrivateKeyFile\: 8bb26d65-47ef-4ca4-a9a8-55b76a1a2ee2.description=
Retrieves network metrics using netstat.  

Inputs\:
host - the system to check
username - the user to log into this system as
password - the password to log in with
name - name of the network interface to check
port - port number for connecting to the host
protocol - the protocol used to run the command (can be one of ssh, ROSH, GlobalShell, Telnet, RSH, local or WMI)
timeout - (optional, default 90 seconds) time in milliseconds to wait for the command to complete
pty - (true, false) whether to use pty
privateKeyFile - The absolute path to the private key file for remote host.
sasHost - the host we want to run the ROSH command on
sasHostUsername - the username used to run the ROSH command on sasHost
usernamePrompt - the prompt that when seen should send the username
passwordPrompt - the prompt that when given should send the password

Responses\:
success - the data was obtained
failure - the data could not be obtained

Result\:
The netstat return string

Extra Results\:
collisions - the collision count
ipAddress - the IP address 
macAddress - the MAC address
receiveBytes - number of received bytes
receiveDrops - number of received drops
receiveErrors - number of received errors
receiveFrameErrors - number of received frame errors
receiveOverruns - number of received overruns
receivePackets - number of received packets
transmitBytes - number of transmitted bytes
transmitCarrierErrors - number of transmitted carrier errors
transmitDrops - number of transmitted drops
transmitErrors - number of transmitted errors
transmitOverruns - number of transmitted overruns
transmitPackets - number of transmitted packets
